  "overview": {
    "summary": "Herb is a Woodsworn created from Laura in the now defunct nation of Saoglas outside the Immortal City of Edelith, and the only one seemingly immune to the corrosion plaguing his kind. He has horrible memory and is adorned with masks able to cast various affects to whoever wears them. He is on a mission to find a way to bring back a beloved figure dear to his mother, and one he shares a body with. The mask he carries is too corroded to be fixed by any normal means. He found Blobert Goopington on his way to the shroud taking the form as a chicken as Herb was feeding them.",
    "personality": "Herb is a curious, sentimental, and clueless idiot, who has moments of genuine clarity and others of idiocacy, he is naturally good hearted and is very impulsive and driven to act in the moment than care about fore or hindsight.",
    "likes":    ["Birds and collecting bird feathers", "Nature", "Adores woodcarving in his free time", "writing about his day in a journal"],
    "dislikes": ["Intrusion of personal space", "Desert", "Wood chippers", "Blueberries"],
    "trivia": [
      { "text": "Herb's race is mostly concentrated to Arvegum", "redacted": false },
      { "text": "He is valued and chosen by the mysterious figure, Rotcio. Who betrayed his entire race and is a vessel of the Corrosion.", "redacted": false },
      { "redacted": true },
      { "redacted": true }
    ],
    "sideQuote": "Knock on Wood"
  },

